<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-10T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-10T12:36:00-05:00" n="1127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1127">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.5034/6</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-10T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>278. Order to notaries provides that information new corporations and
                            particularly those for exploration exploitation oil lands charter shall
                            contain clause providing that foreign stockholders renounce their
                            national rights as to company affairs, this meaning they waive all right
                            to protection interest through their national representatives. Informed
                            that this has been tried before but failed and is not considered to have
                            legal effect. Nevertheless it is undoubtedly dangerous and presumably
                            contrary to treaty rights. Have filed general protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>